title <size:18>Word Processor using Flyweight Pattern (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "User types 'hello hello'. 10 characters but only 4 unique CharacterStyle objects (h,e,l,o). Flyweight shares them. Massive memory savings."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: DOCUMENT — Entry Point
' ====================================================================
class Document {
    - pages : List<Page>
    - characterFactory : CharacterStyleFactory
    - undoStack : List<Command>
    --
    + addCharacter(char, row, col, font, size, color, bold, italic) : void
    + deleteCharacter(row, col) : void
    + applyStyle(fromRow, fromCol, toRow, toCol, font, size, color) : void
    + getPage(index) : Page
    + render() : void
    + undo() : void
    + getMemoryUsage() : long
}

note top of Document #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "User opens a word processor and types text.
    Document is the entry point. It owns pages
    and a **CharacterStyleFactory** (the Flyweight
    factory). Every addCharacter() call goes through
    the factory to share style objects."

    "Key insight: a 10,000 word document has ~50,000
    characters but maybe only 20 unique styles
    (font+size+color+bold+italic combos). Flyweight
    shares those 20 objects across 50,000 characters."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: PAGE + CHARACTER — Extrinsic State
' ====================================================================
class Page {
    - rows : List<Row>
    - pageNumber : int
    --
    + getRow(index) : Row
    + addRow(row) : void
    + render() : void
}

class Row {
    - characters : List<Character>
    - lineHeight : double
    --
    + addCharacter(character) : void
    + removeCharacter(col) : void
    + getCharacter(col) : Character
    + render() : void
}

class Character {
    - charValue : char
    - row : int
    - column : int
    - style : CharacterStyle
    --
    + Character(charValue, row, col, style)
    + getChar() : char
    + getRow() : int
    + getColumn() : int
    + getStyle() : CharacterStyle
    + render() : void
}

note top of Character #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Each character on screen.**
    "**Character** holds:
    - charValue: 'h', 'e', 'l', 'o' (the letter)
    - row, column: position on page
    - style: **pointer to shared CharacterStyle**"

    "charValue + row + column = **extrinsic state**
    (unique per character, stored here)."

    "style = **reference to intrinsic state**
    (shared via Flyweight, NOT duplicated)."

    "Document -> Page -> Row -> Character.
    Standard composition hierarchy."
end note

Document *-- Page : has pages >
Page *-- Row : has rows >
Row *-- Character : has chars >
Character --> CharacterStyle : shares (flyweight) >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: CHARACTER STYLE — The Flyweight Object (KEY)
' ====================================================================
class CharacterStyle <<Flyweight>> {
    - fontFamily : String
    - fontSize : int
    - color : Color
    - isBold : bool
    - isItalic : bool
    - isUnderline : bool
    --
    + CharacterStyle(font, size, color, bold, italic, underline)
    + getFontFamily() : String
    + getFontSize() : int
    + getColor() : Color
    + isBold() : bool
    + isItalic() : bool
    + isUnderline() : bool
    + getKey() : String
    + equals(other) : bool
    + hashCode() : int
}

class Color {
    - red : int
    - green : int
    - blue : int
    --
    + Color(r, g, b)
    + toHex() : String
}

note top of CharacterStyle #FFE0B2
    **STEP 3 - The Flyweight object. (KEY STEP)**
    "**CharacterStyle** is the intrinsic state:
    font, size, color, bold, italic, underline."

    "**This object is SHARED, not duplicated.**
    In a 50,000 character document:"

    "WITHOUT Flyweight:
    50,000 CharacterStyle objects.
    Each ~100 bytes. Total: ~5 MB."

    "WITH Flyweight:
    ~20 unique CharacterStyle objects shared.
    50,000 Characters hold pointers (~8 bytes each).
    Total: ~400 KB. **12x savings.**"

    "**Immutable**: once created, CharacterStyle
    never changes. This is critical — if shared
    objects were mutable, changing one would
    affect all characters using it."
    **Pattern: Flyweight (intrinsic state) | Immutable**
end note

CharacterStyle --> Color


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: CHARACTER STYLE FACTORY — Flyweight Factory (KEY)
' ====================================================================
class CharacterStyleFactory <<FlyweightFactory>> {
    - styleCache : Map<String, CharacterStyle>
    --
    + getStyle(font, size, color, bold, italic, underline) : CharacterStyle
    + getCacheSize() : int
    + getMemorySaved() : long
    + clearCache() : void
    - buildKey(font, size, color, bold, italic, underline) : String
}

note top of CharacterStyleFactory #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - The Flyweight Factory. (KEY STEP)**
    "The single most important class in this design."

    "**getStyle(Arial, 12, Black, false, false, false):**
    1. Build cache key: 'Arial-12-#000000-false-false-false'
    2. Check styleCache map.
    3. If key exists: **return existing object** (shared!)
    4. If not: create new CharacterStyle, store in
       cache, return it."

    "**This is the Flyweight Pattern in action.**
    No matter how many characters use 'Arial 12pt
    Black Normal', only ONE CharacterStyle object
    exists in memory. All characters point to it."

    "getCacheSize(): how many unique styles exist.
    getMemorySaved(): (totalChars - cacheSize) *
    sizeof(CharacterStyle)."
    **Pattern: Flyweight Factory | Memory Efficiency**
end note

CharacterStyleFactory o--> CharacterStyle : caches >
Document --> CharacterStyleFactory : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: INTRINSIC vs EXTRINSIC — The Core Concept
' ====================================================================
note as FLYWEIGHT_CONCEPT #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Intrinsic vs Extrinsic. (EXPLAIN THIS)**
    "The Flyweight Pattern splits object state into two:"

    "**INTRINSIC STATE (shared, inside Flyweight):**
    - fontFamily: 'Arial'
    - fontSize: 12
    - color: Black
    - isBold: false
    - isItalic: false
    - isUnderline: false
    Stored ONCE in CharacterStyle. Shared by many."

    "**EXTRINSIC STATE (unique, outside Flyweight):**
    - charValue: 'h' (the actual letter)
    - row: 3 (which line)
    - column: 7 (which position)
    Stored in each Character. Unique per character."

    "**Why this split?** The intrinsic state is the
    SAME for hundreds of characters. Duplicating
    {Arial, 12, Black, normal} 500 times wastes
    memory. Share one object, store only the
    unique parts (letter + position) per character."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: STYLE COMMAND — Undo Support (Command Pattern)
' ====================================================================
interface StyleCommand <<Command>> {
    + execute() : void
    + undo() : void
}

class ApplyStyleCommand {
    - document : Document
    - fromRow : int
    - fromCol : int
    - toRow : int
    - toCol : int
    - newStyle : CharacterStyle
    - previousStyles : Map<Position, CharacterStyle>
    --
    + execute() : void
    + undo() : void
}

class InsertCharCommand {
    - document : Document
    - charValue : char
    - row : int
    - col : int
    - style : CharacterStyle
    --
    + execute() : void
    + undo() : void
}

class DeleteCharCommand {
    - document : Document
    - deletedChar : Character
    - row : int
    - col : int
    --
    + execute() : void
    + undo() : void
}

note bottom of StyleCommand #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - Undo support.**
    "User selects text and makes it Bold.
    **Command Pattern** — each action is an object."

    "**ApplyStyleCommand**: saves previous styles,
    applies new style (gets from Factory — shared!).
    undo() restores previous styles."

    "**InsertCharCommand**: inserts character.
    undo() removes it."

    "**DeleteCharCommand**: saves deleted character.
    undo() re-inserts it."

    "Document.undoStack stores commands for Ctrl+Z."
    **Pattern: Command | SRP, OCP**
end note

StyleCommand <|.. ApplyStyleCommand
StyleCommand <|.. InsertCharCommand
StyleCommand <|.. DeleteCharCommand
Document o--> StyleCommand : undo stack >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: TEXT FORMATTING — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface TextFormatter <<Strategy>> {
    + format(rows, pageWidth) : List<Row>
}

class LeftAlignFormatter {
    + format(rows, pageWidth) : List<Row>
}

class CenterAlignFormatter {
    + format(rows, pageWidth) : List<Row>
}

class JustifyFormatter {
    + format(rows, pageWidth) : List<Row>
}

class RightAlignFormatter {
    + format(rows, pageWidth) : List<Row>
}

note bottom of TextFormatter #C8E6C9
    **STEP 7 - Text alignment.**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — alignment is pluggable.
    LeftAlign, CenterAlign, Justify, RightAlign.
    Each formats rows differently within page width."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP**
end note

TextFormatter <|.. LeftAlignFormatter
TextFormatter <|.. CenterAlignFormatter
TextFormatter <|.. JustifyFormatter
TextFormatter <|.. RightAlignFormatter
Document --> TextFormatter : formats with >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: RENDERING — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface RenderStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + render(document) : void
}

class ScreenRenderer {
    + render(document) : void
}

class PrintRenderer {
    - dpi : int
    --
    + render(document) : void
}

class PDFExportRenderer {
    - outputPath : String
    --
    + render(document) : void
}

note bottom of RenderStrategy #C8E6C9
    **STEP 8 - How to display/export.**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — rendering is pluggable.
    Screen (WYSIWYG), Print (with margins/DPI),
    PDF export."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP**
end note

RenderStrategy <|.. ScreenRenderer
RenderStrategy <|.. PrintRenderer
RenderStrategy <|.. PDFExportRenderer
Document --> RenderStrategy : renders via >


' ====================================================================
'  MEMORY VISUALIZATION
' ====================================================================
note as MEMORY #FFFDE7
    **Memory savings visualization.**

    "Document: 'hello hello' (10 characters)"

    "**WITHOUT Flyweight (naive):**
    h -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)
    e -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)
    l -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)
    l -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)
    o -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)
    h -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)  DUPLICATE!
    e -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)  DUPLICATE!
    l -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)  DUPLICATE!
    l -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)  DUPLICATE!
    o -> {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N}  (100 bytes)  DUPLICATE!
    Total style memory: 10 * 100 = **1,000 bytes**"

    "**WITH Flyweight:**
    Cache: {Arial,12,Black,N,N,N} -> StyleObj#1
    h -> pointer to StyleObj#1  (8 bytes)
    e -> pointer to StyleObj#1  (8 bytes)
    l -> pointer to StyleObj#1  (8 bytes)
    ...all 10 -> pointer to StyleObj#1
    Total: 1 * 100 + 10 * 8 = **180 bytes**
    **Savings: 82%**"

    "At scale (50,000 chars, 20 unique styles):
    Without: 50,000 * 100 = 5,000,000 bytes (5 MB)
    With:    20 * 100 + 50,000 * 8 = 402,000 bytes (400 KB)
    **Savings: 92%**"
end note


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "User types text. Each character has a position
    (extrinsic) and a style (intrinsic). **CharacterStyleFactory**
    caches unique styles — 50,000 characters share ~20 style objects.
    **Flyweight Pattern** = share immutable intrinsic state,
    store unique extrinsic state separately."

    "Supporting patterns: **Command** (undo/redo for style changes
    + insert/delete), **Strategy** (text alignment + rendering).
    The Flyweight is the star — explain the intrinsic/extrinsic
    split and the memory math."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LAYOUT
' ====================================================================
CharacterStyleFactory -[hidden]down-> FLYWEIGHT_CONCEPT
FLYWEIGHT_CONCEPT -[hidden]down-> MEMORY


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= Key Point |
    | 1 | Document: addCharacter(), applyStyle(), render() | Entry Point | Uses CharacterStyleFactory for all styles |
    | 2 | Document -> Page -> Row -> Character (extrinsic: char + position) | Composition | Character holds pointer to shared style |
    | 3 | CharacterStyle: font, size, color, bold, italic (intrinsic, immutable) | Flyweight Object | Shared, never duplicated, never mutated |
    | 4 | Factory: getStyle() returns cached object or creates new one | Flyweight Factory | Cache key = font+size+color+bold+italic |
    | 5 | Intrinsic (shared style) vs Extrinsic (unique char+position) | Core Concept | The split that enables sharing |
    | 6 | ApplyStyle / InsertChar / DeleteChar commands with undo | Command | Ctrl+Z support |
    | 7 | LeftAlign / Center / Justify / RightAlign formatting | Strategy | Pluggable text alignment |
    | 8 | Screen / Print / PDF rendering | Strategy | Pluggable output |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **50,000 chars, 20 unique styles: WITHOUT Flyweight = 5 MB. WITH Flyweight = 400 KB. 92% savings.** |  |  |
endlegend

@enduml
